(EXCLAIMS IN PAIN)

08:40.770 --> 08:42.522
(PANTING) Oh.

08:42.605 --> 08:44.448
I thought you were the heat.

08:45.275 --> 08:46.527
Do I look like heat?

08:46.609 --> 08:48.156
You look like one
crazy son of a bitch

08:48.236 --> 08:50.113
for a preacher,
I'll tell ya that.

08:50.196 --> 08:52.198
(GROANS)

08:53.825 --> 08:55.702
Who's that guy back
there in the wheat?

08:57.037 --> 08:58.584
Old friend.

08:59.330 --> 09:01.753
With friends like that,
you don't need enemies.

09:06.963 --> 09:08.135
Which way are we headed?

09:09.257 --> 09:10.304
We?

09:11.217 --> 09:13.140
All right, which way
are you headed?

09:13.219 --> 09:14.596
South.

09:15.013 --> 09:17.015
South's all right with me.

09:18.808 --> 09:20.981
You must like my drivin'.

09:21.394 --> 09:22.737
Oh, I love it.

09:22.812 --> 09:24.780
Ever thought of doin'
it professionally?

09:24.856 --> 09:26.153
What?

09:26.232 --> 09:28.781
- Driving.
- Why?

09:31.279 --> 09:32.906
You got blue eyes.

09:32.989 --> 09:36.038
All great race champions have
blue eyes. That's a fact.

09:36.117 --> 09:39.542
And all preachers drink like fish.
That's another fact.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.667
What's your name, boy?

09:45.919 --> 09:47.296
Lightfoot.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.298
You Indian?

09:50.340 --> 09:52.138
Nope, just American.

09:54.260 --> 09:57.355
<i>(WHERE DO I GO FROM HERE PLAYING)</i>

09:57.430 --> 10:02.027
<i>If I knew the way,
I'd go back home</i>

10:03.603 --> 10:06.732
<i>But the countryside
has changed so much</i>

10:06.815 --> 10:09.910
<i>I 'd surely end up lost</i>

10:10.610 --> 10:16.288
<i>Half-remembered names
and faces so far in the past</i>

10:16.366 --> 10:22.749
<i>On the other side of bridges that
were burned once they were crossed</i>

10:22.831 --> 10:26.381
<i>Tell me where,
where does a fool go</i>

10:26.459 --> 10:29.554
<i>When there's no
one left to listen</i>

