It's cold up here.

10:59.951 --> 11:01.043
How's your arm?

11:01.119 --> 11:02.621
Feels like lead.

11:02.704 --> 11:04.706
Give me your belt, will ya?

11:05.373 --> 11:07.000
Your belt, c'mon!

11:15.758 --> 11:17.601
(GRUNTING IN PAIN)

12:09.979 --> 12:12.607
(SCREAMING IN PAIN)
Oh, my God!

12:23.701 --> 12:26.329
You ain't no country preacher,
preacher.

12:27.497 --> 12:29.841
I can tell ya that. Who are ya?

12:36.214 --> 12:37.934
Where are the license
plates for that thing?

12:38.466 --> 12:41.811
Don't have any. I bagged it short of
about five minutes before I ran into you.

12:43.012 --> 12:44.764
Almost ran into you.

12:46.266 --> 12:47.609
(EXHALES)

12:48.434 --> 12:49.731
You like to spend money, boy?

12:49.852 --> 12:51.024
Yeah, when I can get it.

12:51.187 --> 12:52.359
Do you care how you get it?

12:53.231 --> 12:55.074
No.
If it doesn't cost me too much.

13:08.288 --> 13:10.461
Howdy. How's business?

13:10.540 --> 13:14.215
Business? In this business, you're
always one step away from bankruptcy.

13:14.669 --> 13:18.299
Funny money, credit, speculation.
That ain't it.

13:18.423 --> 13:22.553
Somewhere in this country's
a little ol' lady with $79.25.

13:22.927 --> 13:25.021
The five cents is
a Buffalo Nickel.

13:25.763 --> 13:26.935
That ain't it.

13:27.390 --> 13:30.314
She ever cashes in her investment,
whole thing'll collapse.

13:30.393 --> 13:32.816
General Motors, the Pentagon,
the two-party system

13:32.895 --> 13:34.818
and the whole shebang.

13:34.897 --> 13:37.400
Arnold,
what is he saying to you?

13:40.778 --> 13:43.076
That's it.
We're all running downhill.

13:43.156 --> 13:46.126
Gotta keep running faster all the
time or we'll all fall down.

13:46.200 --> 13:49.374
Arnold,
what was he saying to you?

13:52.040 --> 13:53.838
Arnold?

13:53.916 --> 13:55.463
What did he say to you?

13:55.585 --> 13:56.928
Did he insult you?

13:57.253 --> 13:59.255
Excuse me,
I don't wish to be forward,

13:59.422 --> 14:01.345
but we'd like to
exchange cars with you.

14:01.424 --> 14:04.348
So the faster you get out,
the better it'll be for your ass.

14:05.011 --> 14:07.184
- Arnold... (SCREAMS) Oh!
- Come on, out.

14:07.263 --> 14:09.436
Arnold! Oh...

14:19.233 --> 14:21.201
I thought we were only gonna
get the plates? (LAUGHS)

14:21.277 --> 14:23.279
Well,
we didn't have a screwdriver.

14:23.613 --> 14:25.536
Hey, look at this, man.

14:26.616 --> 14:28.493
Look, they got a whole
department store back here.

14:28.576 --> 14:29.616
- Yeah.
- Hey, I like that.

14:29.660 --> 14:32.379
Those clothes and your mouth,
you could be a big man.

14:45.343 --> 14:46.765
Yeah, busy night.

14:48.137 --> 14:50.310
LIGHTFOOT:
I never paid for it in my life.

14:50.973 --> 14:53.067
Sometimes you have
to pay for pleasure.

14:53.142 --> 14:56.021
(LAUGHS) Not me. I'll never pay
for it, I can tell you that.

14:57.563 --> 14:59.782
Well, this is where I get out.

14:59.982 --> 15:03.327
You sure don't know a good
thing when you see it, do you?

15:05.822 --> 15:08.792
Hey, why don't you
take this watch, huh?

15:09.367 --> 15:11.244
I want you to have it.

15:12.829 --> 15:15.002
I don't want your watch, man.

15:16.165 --> 15:17.417
I want your friendship.

15:19.335 --> 15:20.928
God damn it,
I like you, that's all.

15:21.003 --> 15:23.005
I thought we were
gettin' to be friends.

15:24.424 --> 15:25.721
We're good together.

15:26.175 --> 15:29.349
Kid, you're ten years too late.

15:32.849 --> 15:34.692
You sure are one lost dude,
aren't you?

15:36.185 --> 15:37.653
(CHUCKLES)

15:42.859 --> 15:44.702
- Thanks again.
- Yeah.

15:46.571 --> 15:47.788
Shit.

15:48.698 --> 15:49.915
You're as young as you feel.

15:57.707 --> 15:59.755
(BUS HONKING)

16:38.080 --> 16:39.457
Hello.

16:39.540 --> 16:42.510
(LAUGHING) Hey, we gotta
stop meetin' like this.

16:42.585 --> 16:44.337
People are going to talk.

16:44.420 --> 16:45.888
Very funny.

16:45.963 --> 16:48.341
No, with a preacher man,
especially.

16:48.633 --> 16:50.886
Where there's smoke,
there's fire, you know?

16:51.010 --> 16:52.011
(LAUGHING)

16:52.720 --> 16:53.721
Yeah.

17:28.214 --> 17:30.967
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

17:58.494 --> 18:00.588
MAN: (IN CAR)
How y'all doin', baby?

18:00.663 --> 18:02.665
Quick, get in! Quick!

18:08.921 --> 18:10.594
Hey, what is this?

18:12.508 --> 18:14.681
Why walk when you can ride?
(CHUCKLES)

18:14.760 --> 18:17.809
You son of a bitch. Stop this car.
Let me outta here right now...

18:17.888 --> 18:21.358
Hey, what's the matter?
Don't you like my face?

18:22.685 --> 18:25.484
You're the best-looking face I've
seen all day. I can tell you that.

18:25.563 --> 18:27.281
And just where the hell do
you think you're taking me?

18:27.356 --> 18:28.949
<i>Anywhere you say, sweetness.</i>

18:29.275 --> 18:30.276
I'm hungry.

18:30.359 --> 18:31.952
Chili, right?

18:35.031 --> 18:36.533
Um... (CHUCKLES)

18:38.784 --> 18:40.752
I didn't get your name.

18:41.370 --> 18:43.122
Oh, I didn't give it to ya.

18:43.205 --> 18:45.003
My name is Lightfoot.

18:45.833 --> 18:47.460
- Lightfoot?
- That's right.

18:47.543 --> 18:51.264
That's a dumb name. I mean, what kind
of a person would name a kid that?

18:51.339 --> 18:52.716
- You know?
- What's your name?

18:53.007 --> 18:54.384
Melody.

18:55.176 --> 18:57.474
Melody?
(LAUGHS) That's not a dumb name?

18:59.972 --> 19:01.064
Hey, maybe we had the same father.

19:01.223 --> 19:02.315
(LAUGHS)

19:03.559 --> 19:05.561
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

19:13.152 --> 19:14.745
Brought back some extra goodies.

19:15.237 --> 19:16.363
Are you outta your mind?

19:16.447 --> 19:18.745
This is Gloria and Melody.

19:18.824 --> 19:21.043
- BOTH: Pleased to meet you.
- Melody, Gloria.

19:21.118 --> 19:22.916
Go right in, ladies.

19:24.205 --> 19:25.752
(CLEARS THROAT)

19:27.333 --> 19:29.210
You're full of all kinds
of surprises, aren't you?

19:29.293 --> 19:31.762
Gloria has a great ass,
doesn't she?

19:31.837 --> 19:33.839
(LAUGHS) It's the best
I've ever seen, really.

19:33.923 --> 19:35.266
Wouldn't you say that, Melody?

19:36.342 --> 19:39.061
Listen, I just got out of a
bed to come here, you know.

19:39.136 --> 19:42.640
And I don't intend to jump
right back into one here.

19:44.225 --> 19:47.149
Oh, I forgot to tell ya.
Gloria is yours.

20:02.076 --> 20:03.293
(GLORIA GIGGLING)

20:03.452 --> 20:04.669
(SPRINGS SQUEAKING)

20:04.745 --> 20:07.498
Take it easy, Gloria.
You're killin' me.

20:08.165 --> 20:10.213
GLORIA: Where did you get
all those scars from?

20:10.292 --> 20:12.135
PREACHER: Marines, Korea.

20:12.294 --> 20:14.672
GLORIA: Oh, yeah?
I heard about that war.

20:20.594 --> 20:22.596
(GRUNTS) Ooh!

20:23.180 --> 20:24.477
(EXHALES)

20:28.519 --> 20:29.691
Mmm...

20:31.147 --> 20:33.115
(MOUTHING)

20:42.241 --> 20:43.493
What are you doin'?

20:43.826 --> 20:44.952
Getting dressed.

20:46.829 --> 20:48.046
Why?

20:48.122 --> 20:50.090
So you can take me home.

20:52.376 --> 20:54.299
What for?
You can stay here tonight.

20:54.378 --> 20:57.348
No, no, I have to get home
before it's light out.

20:57.548 --> 20:59.926
Look, if you think I'm leavin'
here at 3:30 in the morning

21:00.009 --> 21:02.182
to take you wherever
the hell home is, you're crazy.

21:03.137 --> 21:04.389
Oh, you'd better take me

21:04.472 --> 21:07.021
or I'll walk out of here
stark-naked and scream "Rape."

21:07.641 --> 21:08.858
Sure you will.

21:09.727 --> 21:10.979
That would be stupid.

21:18.944 --> 21:20.366
GLORIA: Rape!

21:22.865 --> 21:24.458
Rape!

21:26.243 --> 21:29.042
- Do you think we should stay here?
- Why not?

21:29.955 --> 21:31.377
Get your clothes on.

21:32.708 --> 21:35.257
Here's some money.
You can take a cab.

22:09.829 --> 22:11.627
Sweets to the sweets!

22:27.930 --> 22:29.227
How did you do?

22:30.140 --> 22:32.142
Red-haired women are bad luck.

23:14.768 --> 23:16.896
You sure that's their car?

23:17.730 --> 23:19.152
That's their hearse.

23:42.504 --> 23:44.302
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)

23:45.591 --> 23:48.185
- Good morning.
- Good morning, sweetness.

23:49.386 --> 23:51.627
- Okay, what'll it be this morning?
- I'm gonna have you.

23:52.514 --> 23:56.360
And four scrambled eggs,
very loose.

24:00.189 --> 24:02.191
Bacon, toast, coffee.

24:03.359 --> 24:05.862
And American fries.
You got American fries?

24:05.986 --> 24:07.738
- Yes.
- American fries?

24:08.948 --> 24:09.949
Right.

24:11.200 --> 24:12.952
Just coffee, black. Thanks.

24:13.369 --> 24:15.246
Okay. Thank you.

24:20.834 --> 24:22.711
(EXCLAIMS) God, it's poetry!

24:22.795 --> 24:23.796
Good jaw.

24:24.213 --> 24:26.511
I love 'em like that.
Nice and tight. Jesus!

24:29.176 --> 24:31.520
How you feelin' today, preacher?

24:33.430 --> 24:35.353
The clock uncoils the working day,

24:35.432 --> 24:38.402
and he wakes up feeling
his youth has gone away.

24:39.478 --> 24:40.878
Now what the hell is that?
A prayer?

24:42.064 --> 24:43.236
A poem.

24:43.941 --> 24:46.535
- A poem? (LAUGHS)
- Poetry.

24:46.860 --> 24:48.032
Ah.

24:48.112 --> 24:50.911
You stick with me, kid.
You can live forever.

24:51.407 --> 24:53.250
(BOTH LAUGH)

25:03.419 --> 25:04.466
Sir.

25:13.804 --> 25:15.602
You big son of a bitch!

26:13.155 --> 26:17.661
You must've been into something
very big, preacher. Very big.

26:22.873 --> 26:24.295
I can't see.

26:28.879 --> 26:30.677
(SHOOTING CONTINUES)

26:34.510 --> 26:36.103
Damn, they're goin' fast.

26:36.178 --> 26:37.771
I can't see 'em.

26:37.971 --> 26:40.411
I don't know how the hell
I could've missed 'em so many times.

26:41.266 --> 26:42.734
(SHOTS FIRED AGAIN)

26:44.019 --> 26:44.438
Shoot.

26:44.464 --> 26:46.138
I think you got...
No, you didn't either.

26:47.356 --> 26:48.699
Hang on!

26:53.153 --> 26:54.826
He went over the...

26:54.905 --> 26:56.828
What do we do now, Red?

26:56.907 --> 26:58.875
Geronimo!

27:12.756 --> 27:14.224
Now, in a case like this,

27:14.299 --> 27:16.677
you can't take your hands off
the wheel even for a second, see.

27:16.760 --> 27:17.886
Get your hands on the wheel.

27:20.055 --> 27:22.979
A rolling stone gathers no moss.
(EXCLAIMS)

27:38.532 --> 27:40.034
(GRUNTS) Shit!

27:45.747 --> 27:47.624
(LIGHTFOOT SHOUTS TRIUMPHANTLY)

28:06.894 --> 28:08.271
What do we do now, Red?

28:08.353 --> 28:10.572
(SPITS)
Shut up, Goody.

28:21.909 --> 28:23.911
(GUN FIRES)

28:24.661 --> 28:26.334
Goddamn ding-ding.

29:01.949 --> 29:03.326
Ah.

29:05.452 --> 29:08.922
Yeah, transmission's finished.
Seals are all gone.

29:10.832 --> 29:12.334
Cadillac's my car anyway.

29:14.461 --> 29:15.929
- Where are we now?
- (SIGHS)

29:16.880 --> 29:18.097
Hells Canyon.

29:18.799 --> 29:20.221
Snake River.

29:22.177 --> 29:24.771
Mostly huntin' camps
and sheep camps.

29:28.684 --> 29:31.813
Up here, people's business
is nobody's but their own.

29:33.188 --> 29:36.488
Hells Canyon delivery boat's gonna come
by pretty soon. <i>The Idaho Dream.</i>

29:36.775 --> 29:38.573
Should take us right up the river.

29:39.403 --> 29:42.031
Better off gettin' as far away
from me as you can, boy.

29:44.533 --> 29:46.535
In for a penny, in for a pound.

29:49.121 --> 29:50.418
(SIGHS)

29:53.667 --> 29:55.419
Lonely country, kid.

29:57.879 --> 29:59.301
(GRUNTS)

30:03.218 --> 30:04.891
You got any people?

30:06.263 --> 30:09.733
(LAUGHS) I don't even know
anymore. That's weird.

30:12.227 --> 30:14.446
Last time I saw any of
them I was just a kid.

30:20.235 --> 30:22.078
I was a little too much for
them to handle, you know.

30:22.154 --> 30:25.283
(CHUCKLES) So, they sent me away
to one of these boarding schools.

30:26.742 --> 30:28.836
And on the train I met this woman.

30:30.287 --> 30:32.039
Oh, man!
(CHUCKLES)

30:33.415 --> 30:34.792
So, the next thing I know,

30:34.875 --> 30:37.344
we're getting off the train
together in New Orleans, right.

30:38.253 --> 30:42.884
Two weeks later,
I wake up in some fleabag hotel.

30:43.925 --> 30:45.927
(LAUGHING) Oh, God!

30:47.220 --> 30:49.723
But we had ourselves a good time.

30:55.145 --> 30:57.065
So, after her, things looked good.
I kept movin'.

30:58.398 --> 31:00.116
Now, you can't stop?

31:01.068 --> 31:03.070
(BOAT HORN BLARING)

31:04.738 --> 31:06.115
Here she is.

31:07.783 --> 31:09.205
<i>Idaho Dream.</i>

31:10.577 --> 31:13.831
(HORN BLARING AGAIN)

31:26.468 --> 31:27.811
(EXHALES)

31:30.847 --> 31:32.849
(HORN BLARES)

31:48.448 --> 31:49.825
Oh, did you see that?

31:49.908 --> 31:52.161
Oh, a steelhead, man.
Beautiful.

31:53.829 --> 31:56.207
- Ah... Did you see that?
- Where?

31:56.957 --> 31:58.049
Yeah.

31:59.418 --> 32:01.341
Well, my good friend,
we're broke.

32:01.420 --> 32:03.593
Do you have any suggestions?

32:05.549 --> 32:08.177
If I knew what you know,
I'd never be broke.

32:09.886 --> 32:13.607
Well, what do you think I know
that you would like to know?

32:14.641 --> 32:16.018
All right.

32:18.895 --> 32:20.863
Well, for one thing,
I'd like to know

32:20.939 --> 32:22.737
if there's a good way
of beating a bank.

32:23.150 --> 32:26.871
(SCOFFS) Banks! What the hell
do you know about banks?

32:26.945 --> 32:29.243
What the hell do you
know about banks?

32:31.408 --> 32:33.456
(PREACHER LAUGHS)

32:33.535 --> 32:34.787
What's so funny?

32:34.870 --> 32:36.247
- You.
- Me? (LAUGHS)

32:36.329 --> 32:37.797
That's right.

32:39.583 --> 32:42.382
Hey, a man can do
whatever he sets his mind to.

32:42.461 --> 32:43.713
Now, me,

32:44.379 --> 32:47.974
I wanna walk in and buy a
white Cadillac convertible.

32:48.049 --> 32:50.723
Actually walk in
and buy it, cash.

33:06.193 --> 33:07.570
(SIGHS)

33:16.661 --> 33:18.914
You might set your mind
to gettin' us a lift.

33:20.373 --> 33:23.217
- Hey!
- This walkin' is tough on my bad leg.

33:24.252 --> 33:27.381
This is the best time. Most state
troopers are having coffee now.

33:32.052 --> 33:34.054
(CAR APPROACHING)

33:40.769 --> 33:42.112
(GRUNTS)

33:44.564 --> 33:46.783
LIGHTFOOT: Hey! Hey!
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

33:47.609 --> 33:48.906
Hey!

33:56.451 --> 33:57.452
(WHOOPS)

33:57.619 --> 33:59.019
That sure isn't
any white Cadillac.

33:59.538 --> 34:01.461
Beggars can't be choosy.

34:01.915 --> 34:04.543
You simple-minded
son of a bitch.

34:07.003 --> 34:08.004
(FIERCE GROWLING)

34:08.088 --> 34:10.637
Get in the back seat.
Get in the back seat.

34:10.799 --> 34:11.925
There's a raccoon in here.

34:12.007 --> 34:14.136
Hell with the raccoon.
Get in the back seat.

34:14.219 --> 34:17.518
Boy, what's the matter with you? I ain't
got all day to wait on you. Come on.

34:19.516 --> 34:21.313
(TIRES SCREECHING)

34:26.856 --> 34:29.905
(JABBERING) I've been...
I'll take you wherever you wanna go.

34:29.985 --> 34:32.579
I've been drivin' all
over this country, man.

34:32.654 --> 34:34.748
This guy another friend of yours?

34:35.322 --> 34:37.917
Slightly advanced, isn't he?

34:37.993 --> 34:39.370
(TIRES SCREECHING)

34:39.452 --> 34:43.252
(DRIVER SLURS INCOHERENTLY)

34:55.885 --> 34:56.976
(LIGHTFOOT COUGHING)

34:57.094 --> 34:58.142
PREACHER: Hey!

34:58.221 --> 34:59.689
- (DRIVER LAUGHING)
- Hey, what's wrong with this wreck?

34:59.764 --> 35:01.311
We're gettin' gassed back here.

35:01.391 --> 35:02.643
(DRIVER LAUGHING)

35:02.726 --> 35:04.728
(DRIVER YELLING INCOHERENTLY)

35:11.026 --> 35:14.826
This guy's a basket case.
He's got the exhaust pipe in here.

35:14.946 --> 35:16.789
(LAUGHING PSYCHOTICALLY)

35:26.666 --> 35:28.668
(COUGHING)

35:34.382 --> 35:36.259
(RABBITS SQUEALING)

35:38.094 --> 35:40.062
He's not your run-of-the-mill
basket case, is he?

35:40.138 --> 35:42.561
This guy is definitely
out to lunch.

35:44.059 --> 35:45.606
(COCKS GUN)

35:45.935 --> 35:48.154
(GUN FIRING)

35:54.235 --> 35:56.112
What the hell's the matter
with you, boy?

35:58.615 --> 36:00.583
(BOTH GRUNTING)

36:01.368 --> 36:02.915
Hey, you're good, man.

36:04.037 --> 36:05.380
Very good.

36:06.081 --> 36:08.049
Glass head, like all these nuts.

36:11.503 --> 36:14.256
I don't know what the hell we're
gonna do with all these rabbits.

36:14.381 --> 36:15.758
Let 'em out.

36:17.967 --> 36:19.969
I saw that.
That was very good.

36:21.221 --> 36:23.849
Where are we headed, man?
I'm ready.

36:24.307 --> 36:26.480
I don't know. Sometimes
when there's nothin' to do,

36:26.559 --> 36:28.607
it's best just to keep movin'.

36:30.021 --> 36:31.944
(SNIFFING)
You smell somethin' up here?

36:33.942 --> 36:35.114
No.

36:35.819 --> 36:37.196
Smell that?

36:37.362 --> 36:39.080
I don't smell anything.

36:39.948 --> 36:41.916
It smells like shit.

36:43.118 --> 36:44.119
Ah...

36:45.537 --> 36:47.255
- Raccoon shit.
- Raccoon shit.

36:48.331 --> 36:51.130
Hang your hand out the window
and let the rain get at it.

36:51.960 --> 36:54.383
- Would you like a little on your...
- No, get outta here!

36:54.462 --> 36:56.806
Just remember not
to pick your teeth.

36:56.881 --> 36:59.851
(LAUGHING) Oh, God.

37:40.967 --> 37:42.435
Now, in these small-town banks,

37:42.510 --> 37:45.980
they leave the telephone off
the hook in the vault at night

37:46.055 --> 37:48.057
so the local operator
can listen in.

37:49.851 --> 37:51.603
People walk into these banks today

37:51.686 --> 37:53.654
with paper sacks, fill 'em full
of money and they walk out.

37:53.730 --> 37:55.152
You see that all the time.

37:55.815 --> 37:57.738
Anybody can do it.

37:58.526 --> 38:00.073
Bullshit.

38:06.576 --> 38:08.328
Now, the newest bank vaults

38:08.411 --> 38:11.460
have walls of reinforced
concrete five feet thick,

38:11.539 --> 38:13.132
backed by six inches of steel.

38:14.375 --> 38:16.469
The vault door is
stainless steel-faced.

38:17.212 --> 38:19.465
It's an inch and a
half of cast steel,

38:19.547 --> 38:22.221
another 12 inches of
burn-resisting steel,

38:22.842 --> 38:26.346
and another inch and a half
of open-hearthed steel.

38:26.805 --> 38:28.148
Come here.

38:29.808 --> 38:33.904
A vault door has 20 bolts,
each an inch in diameter.

38:33.978 --> 38:36.652
Eight on each side, eight on the
other, two top and two bottom.

38:36.731 --> 38:38.028
(LAUGHS)

38:38.149 --> 38:41.073
This holds the door into a 16-inch
steel jamb set in 18 inches of concrete

38:41.653 --> 38:44.156
which is crosshatched
by steel bars

38:44.239 --> 38:46.492
running both vertical
and horizontal.

38:46.616 --> 38:47.896
Now, this door is precision-made

38:47.909 --> 38:51.004
so you can't pour nitro in between
the seam of the door and the vault.

38:51.788 --> 38:52.835
Yeah.

38:52.956 --> 38:54.116
(SIGHS) If that isn't enough,

38:56.417 --> 38:58.840
there's microphones,
electric eyes,

38:58.920 --> 39:02.595
pressure-sensitive mats,
vibration detectors, tear gas,

39:03.216 --> 39:06.345
and even thermostats that detect
the slightest rise in temperature.

39:08.096 --> 39:09.689
You still interested
in banks, kid?

39:09.764 --> 39:12.438
- I knew you weren't a preacher. (LAUGHS)
- Shit.

39:13.268 --> 39:15.612
Preaching isn't so bad.
You get used to it.

39:16.729 --> 39:18.197
Uh, you are what you do,
so to speak.

39:18.273 --> 39:20.275
At times I even forgot
about the money.

39:21.484 --> 39:22.952
What money?

39:27.615 --> 39:29.242
Montana Armored.

39:31.119 --> 39:32.746
Montana Armored?

39:34.789 --> 39:36.791
How did you get into the vault?

39:38.209 --> 39:41.088
(EXHALES) 20 mm cannon
with armor-piercing shells.

39:41.296 --> 39:42.969
Wasn't too hard.

39:43.423 --> 39:44.891
Hey, that was on the news.

39:44.966 --> 39:47.139
That was a big deal.
What did they call that guy?

39:48.052 --> 39:49.645
The Thunderbolt.

39:52.473 --> 39:53.816
That's you.

39:54.392 --> 39:56.269
(LAUGHS) You're the Thunderbolt.

39:56.352 --> 39:58.275
Mmm-hmm, parson's luck.

39:59.063 --> 40:01.065
Oh, no!

40:01.149 --> 40:02.742
Watch out for the dog shit.

40:04.193 --> 40:05.319
Thunderbolt!

40:05.445 --> 40:07.368
(LAUGHS)

40:07.447 --> 40:09.870
Thunderbolt and Lightfoot. That
sounds like something, doesn't it?

40:09.949 --> 40:12.748
You're forgetting I'm a hell
of a lot older than you are kid.

40:12.827 --> 40:14.467
Hey, there are plenty
of guys twice my age

40:14.495 --> 40:16.042
who don't know their ass
from a hole in the ground.

40:16.122 --> 40:17.749
I won't fault you there.

40:17.832 --> 40:19.254
In for a penny, in for a pound.

40:19.334 --> 40:21.962
So, who are these guys
that are following us?

40:22.045 --> 40:23.342
Oh...

40:24.672 --> 40:27.596
The big dude's a war hero.

40:27.675 --> 40:31.020
His name's Red Leary.
Saved my life once in Korea.

40:31.095 --> 40:35.316
He was sent to prison in Illinois
later on for stabbing a woman.

40:35.391 --> 40:38.486
There he met an old-time bank
robber, named Billy Lamb.

40:38.561 --> 40:40.279
Lamb taught him
how to break safes.

40:42.023 --> 40:44.367
Lamb was a real
genius for organization.

40:45.193 --> 40:46.695
Thanks.

40:49.113 --> 40:51.707
When they got out,
Lamb introduced him to Dunlop,

40:51.783 --> 40:54.036
Dunlop's an electronics
expert or was.

40:54.118 --> 40:56.416
That's the guy you took
care of in the field.

40:59.332 --> 41:01.300
- Wanna brew?
- Definitely.

41:01.376 --> 41:04.971
The little Orphan Annie-eyed
character's Eddie Goody.

41:06.381 --> 41:08.600
He's a driver.
He's harmless when he's alone.

41:08.675 --> 41:10.052
So, what happened to the money?

41:11.135 --> 41:13.558
Hey, I don't care anything about
the money, you know that.

41:15.223 --> 41:17.476
We're friends, right?
I like you as a friend.

41:17.558 --> 41:19.060
Yeah.

41:21.688 --> 41:25.363
Oh, we hid it in a one-room
schoolhouse in Warsaw, Montana.

41:25.441 --> 41:27.660
A place Lamb went to
when he was a kid.

41:29.112 --> 41:31.786
Hid it in the wall
right behind the blackboard.

41:31.864 --> 41:34.208
Half a million dollars-worth.
It's still there.

41:34.283 --> 41:35.455
Schoolhouse?

41:35.535 --> 41:36.787
Right behind the blackboard.

41:36.869 --> 41:37.916
Why?

41:39.914 --> 41:41.837
Well, it was always Lamb's
practice to control the money

41:41.916 --> 41:43.418
till the final split.

41:44.544 --> 41:45.905
We kept in contact
with each other

41:45.920 --> 41:47.342
through personals
in the newspaper.

41:48.631 --> 41:50.725
Then Lamb had a heart
attack and died.

41:50.800 --> 41:52.894
Guess he was just too old for it.

41:52.969 --> 41:54.767
Leary got suspicious
but I wasn't about to tell him

41:54.846 --> 41:57.019
where the hell the money was,

41:57.098 --> 41:59.772
because I knew he'd go straight
to it, heat or no heat.

42:02.854 --> 42:06.358
Well, then the police
released a thing in the press

42:06.441 --> 42:08.364
saying that the money
had been found.

42:08.443 --> 42:09.786
Bullshit.

42:09.861 --> 42:11.283
Leary went off his ass.

42:12.947 --> 42:15.575
He got careless but he couldn't
lead them to the money

42:15.658 --> 42:17.378
'cause he didn't know
where the hell it was.

42:19.620 --> 42:22.965
Finally, they arrested and convicted
him on another bank robbery

42:23.041 --> 42:24.793
that took place
several years before.

42:26.044 --> 42:28.638
And when he got out he convinced
the others I'd set him up.

42:29.756 --> 42:32.760
I decided best that I should
drop out for a while.

42:35.762 --> 42:37.242
That church was a
pretty far-out idea.

42:37.305 --> 42:38.932
Hmm.

42:39.015 --> 42:42.064
About as far out as possible,
I thought.

42:44.437 --> 42:45.529
Fuck!

43:00.745 --> 43:02.247
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

43:26.145 --> 43:27.613
Are you sure this is the spot?

43:29.148 --> 43:30.525
Yeah.

43:30.608 --> 43:32.360
What?
I didn't hear what you said.

43:32.443 --> 43:33.945
I said, yeah, this is it.

43:38.199 --> 43:39.371
Well, what happened to it?

43:41.035 --> 43:43.538
I don't know. Progress.

44:02.056 --> 44:03.729
(TAPS FLAGPOLE)

44:14.694 --> 44:15.911
Have a nice day, boy.

44:18.531 --> 44:19.953
Here, for you.

44:20.741 --> 44:22.163
That's the last of our money.

44:25.079 --> 44:26.331
It's good.

44:27.206 --> 44:28.207
Real good.

44:55.651 --> 44:56.994
Fantastic pistachio.

44:59.363 --> 45:00.535
What do we do now?

45:01.365 --> 45:03.413
Drop your cocks and
reach for your socks.

45:05.870 --> 45:07.713
Don't look at me.
I didn't say a word.

45:08.956 --> 45:10.128
- Red?
- Start the car.

45:12.376 --> 45:13.593
Freeze, you son of a bitch.

45:13.669 --> 45:15.171
The first one of
you moves I shoot.

45:18.758 --> 45:20.977
(ENGINE REVVING)

45:51.540 --> 45:53.634
All right, kill the engine.

45:53.709 --> 45:55.382
Hand me the keys and
don't turn around.

45:59.173 --> 46:01.392
Now, both of you get out
of Pistachio's side.

46:01.467 --> 46:04.016
No ideas, you'll both be dead
before you hit the ground.

46:05.513 --> 46:06.560
Move it.

46:19.235 --> 46:20.657
Turn around.

46:23.489 --> 46:24.706
The guy's in the car.

46:26.075 --> 46:27.702
That's it, smartass.

46:29.120 --> 46:30.713
Red. Goody.

46:32.331 --> 46:33.799
How's Dunlop?

46:33.874 --> 46:35.376
That's for us to know
and you to find out.

46:35.501 --> 46:36.627
Shut up, Goody.

46:39.880 --> 46:41.001
Well, what do you want, Red?

46:41.048 --> 46:42.300
What do I want?

46:43.217 --> 46:44.764
You got balls.
I'll say that for you, Johnny.

46:44.844 --> 46:47.438
I want your ass, that's what
I want, my friend.

46:47.555 --> 46:49.435
Hey, flattery's not gonna
get you guys anywhere.

46:49.473 --> 46:50.474
(LAUGHS)

46:51.684 --> 46:53.152
Who's the comedian?

46:53.227 --> 46:54.854
Name's Lightfoot.

46:54.937 --> 46:56.189
Does he know everything?

46:56.272 --> 46:57.273
- No.
- Yeah.

47:02.194 --> 47:03.241
Lightfoot, huh?

47:04.405 --> 47:05.497
Yeah.

47:06.240 --> 47:07.412
(GROANING)

47:14.498 --> 47:15.795
It's a good thing
I didn't hit him in the face.

47:15.875 --> 47:17.548
He'd be dead now.

47:17.626 --> 47:19.845
You always had
a high opinion of yourself, Red.

47:20.755 --> 47:22.475
What have you been
preaching lately, Johnny?

47:23.257 --> 47:24.554
Survival.

47:27.845 --> 47:31.065
- Are you ready?
- I've been counting the days.

47:36.562 --> 47:38.030
(GRUNTING)

47:41.567 --> 47:42.784
That's for the kid.

47:43.652 --> 47:45.404
Now, do you wanna talk
or you wanna play games?

47:45.488 --> 47:46.785
What do you want me to do, Red?

47:48.616 --> 47:50.334
Shut your face.

47:50.409 --> 47:51.956
(GROANING)

47:56.499 --> 47:58.172
(PANTING)

48:05.216 --> 48:06.513
(GROANING)

48:07.968 --> 48:09.094
(GASPS)

48:09.178 --> 48:11.146
I can't breathe! I got asthma.

48:13.557 --> 48:15.651
What do you want
me to do now, Red?

48:15.726 --> 48:17.569
Kill the son of a bitch.

48:17.645 --> 48:18.771
Here?

48:19.522 --> 48:21.024
Yes.

48:21.107 --> 48:22.575
Now?

48:22.650 --> 48:23.697
Now!

48:25.903 --> 48:27.701
Don't ever point a gun at me.
Understand?

48:27.780 --> 48:28.781
Not even a twig.

48:30.282 --> 48:31.283
You got it.

48:31.784 --> 48:33.224
You come from the
hitters, don't you?

48:38.416 --> 48:39.759
What are you waiting for?

48:40.167 --> 48:41.927
Why don't you kill me?
I would've killed you.

48:42.920 --> 48:44.547
(RED GASPING)

48:51.679 --> 48:53.679
That doesn't make up
for a difference in two years.

48:53.681 --> 48:55.274
I'm gonna kill you anyway.

48:55.349 --> 48:58.148
The money was here,
in the schoolhouse.

49:00.646 --> 49:02.023
What's this garbage talking about?

49:03.858 --> 49:05.201
The money was never recovered.

49:07.528 --> 49:10.077
The TV, and the radio, the papers,
everybody was lying.

49:10.156 --> 49:12.124
They were working with the police.

49:12.199 --> 49:13.542
When Lamb died I...

49:14.326 --> 49:15.327
I never came back here.

49:15.411 --> 49:16.754
The money's still here.
It's safe.

49:16.829 --> 49:17.921
Here?

49:18.873 --> 49:21.968
Yeah. Lamb went
to school here in Warsaw,

49:22.042 --> 49:23.794
a little one-room schoolhouse.

49:23.878 --> 49:26.802
We put the money in the wall,
behind the blackboard.

49:26.881 --> 49:28.554
Where's this one-room schoolhouse?

49:29.717 --> 49:30.809
Gone.

49:31.719 --> 49:33.767
Gone? Gone where?

49:36.390 --> 49:37.607
I wish I knew.

49:37.683 --> 49:40.357
Used to be right where the
new schoolhouse is now.

49:40.436 --> 49:42.234
You expect me to
believe all this crap?

49:44.440 --> 49:46.442
It's the sad-ass truth, Red.

49:46.525 --> 49:48.619
Why do you think I'd come
to a dumb town like this?

49:48.694 --> 49:49.946
RED:
How the hell do I know?

49:50.029 --> 49:52.282
You're queer for dumb towns.

49:52.364 --> 49:54.583
Half a million dollars just
don't disappear like that.

49:54.658 --> 49:57.058
They should've found something
when they tore the place down.

49:58.245 --> 49:59.667
I wish I had the answer for you.

50:04.418 --> 50:06.671
The sad part is that we
got away with it.

50:08.297 --> 50:10.049
It's a sin, that's what it is.

50:11.550 --> 50:12.802
Christ, it's a sin.

50:14.678 --> 50:16.021
Oh.

50:16.096 --> 50:17.439
Boy, I feel old.

50:19.642 --> 50:21.360
What are we gonna do now, Red?

50:22.019 --> 50:23.271
Shut up, Goody.

50:24.730 --> 50:25.947
(SNEEZES)

50:28.067 --> 50:29.319
I got hay fever too.

50:43.707 --> 50:45.380
Why not do it again?

50:45.459 --> 50:47.086
What's he mouthing off about now?

50:47.169 --> 50:50.264
Montana Armored. We hit the
same place, the same way.

50:50.339 --> 50:51.807
- Montana Armored?
- Yeah?

50:52.299 --> 50:53.721
(LAUGHS)

50:56.512 --> 50:57.638
What?

50:57.805 --> 50:59.148
(BOTH LAUGHING)

50:59.557 --> 51:01.025
Hey, they'd never expect it.

51:01.100 --> 51:03.523
Not something that big.

51:03.602 --> 51:05.730
It's never been done
before, has it?

51:05.813 --> 51:07.941
Oh, that'd really be something,
wouldn't it?

51:09.984 --> 51:11.236
Yeah, it sure would.

51:12.695 --> 51:14.868
